* {{tbox|pic=Tiny fish detail.png|Suddenly, a tiny fish darts out of the sand and takes the bait!}}
* '''Player:''' Well, this fish seems hilariously small. Still, if it's the only fish, there's a chance I can win the contest. I should show it to Larry.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Big Dave afterwards====
* {{tcond|If the player has not completed [[Fishing Contest]]:}}
** '''Big Dave:''' Hey guy! Always nice to see a fresh face!
** '''Player:''' Hey, who are you?
** '''Big Dave:''' The name's Big Dave! Current champion of the Hemenster fishing contest.
** '''Big Dave:''' I heard there'd be a fishing contest 'round here, so I came to win it.
* {{tcond|If the player has completed Fishing Contest:}}
** '''Big Dave:''' Hey, don't I know you from the Hemenster fishing contest?
** '''Player:''' Big Dave? What are you doing here?
** '''Big Dave:''' Well, I heard there'd be a fishing contest 'round here, so I came to win it.
* '''Big Dave:''' It's strange, though. Doesn't seem like there's even anything in the pond...
* '''Player:''' Well I did manage to catch something, but it's not exactly a prize-winning catch...
* '''Big Dave:''' You caught something?! That's incredible! How did you do it?
* '''Player:''' This is a contest, isn't it? I'm not going to tell my secrets, if that's alright!
* '''Big Dave:''' Hah! Alright then, keep your secrets!
* '''Big Dave:''' But seriously, nobody else has caught a thing yet. I reckon you should show that to Larry.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Larry===
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Ah, hello there! Any luck wit' the fish?
* '''Player:''' Well, I caught this fish. What do you reckon?
* {{tbox|pic=Tiny fish detail.png|You hand over your catch.}}
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Hmm... yep, 'tis a fish.
* '''Player:''' So do I win the contest?
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Well, I dunno... I s'pose nobody else has caught anythin' yet.
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Tell ye what, I'm happy callin' ye the winner if ye promise not to let Hassan know I've spent the entire thing on me backside.
* '''Player:''' Uh..... sure.
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Cheers, matey! I'll send someone up to let Hassan know ye've won. All the best!
* {{tact|end}}

===After winning the contest===
====Talking to Dave after winning the contest====
* '''Big Dave:''' Congratulations! I heard you won the fishing contest!
* '''Player:''' Thanks, Dave!
* {{tcond|If the player has not completed [[Fishing Contest]]:}}
** '''Big Dave:''' Even if I didn't win, this has been a fun trip out for me. You should come try and win the fishing contest in Hemenster; there's some REAL big fish out there!
* {{tcond|If the player has completed Fishing Contest:}}
** '''Big Dave:''' Even if I didn't win, this has been a fun trip out for me. Hopefully I'll see you back in Hemenster one day!
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Ali Morrisane after winning the contest====
* {{topt|Talk about the birthday event.}}
** '''Ali Morrisane:''' Congratulations, friend! I heard you won the fishing contest!
** '''Player:''' Thanks, Ali! I couldn't have done it without your help!
** '''Ali Morrisane:''' I can assure you friend, your delivery of the trade report has helped me more than you could possibly know!
** '''Ali Morrisane:''' There's just a few minor details I need to smooth over.
** '''Player:''' Anything I can help with?
** '''Ali Morrisane:''' Perhaps in time, friend.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=No|Talk about something else.}}

====Talking to Larry Leprechaun after winning the contest====
* '''Player:''' So why are you just sat here?
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' To be honest, matey, I didn't really want te host the fishin' contest. I just wanted te get a tan!
* '''Larry Leprechaun:''' Still, Captain Dalbur's decent company. Talks a lot about how adventurers sometimes deliver food out here. Need t' see how I can get in on that.
* {{tact|end}}

==My Arm's Cook Off==
===Interacting with cooking supplies===
* {{tcond|Before asking My Arm to participate:}}
** '''My Arm:''' Hey, you can only use that if you're taking part in the cookout!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|After asking My Arm to participate, but before speaking to contestants:}}
** '''Player:''' I don't think I'm ready to use this yet.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to My Arm===
{{Incomplete|Some of this dialogue is unavailable to players who have not completed the [[My Arm's Big Adventure]] and [[Making Friends with My Arm]] quests.}}
* '''Player:''' Hey, My Arm.
* '''My Arm:''' Are you here for cookoff?
* '''Player:''' Yes, I'd like to join please!
* '''My Arm:''' I t'ink that is okay. You are bit late though, others already dun. Not many ingredients left.
* {{tcond|If the player completed [[My Arm's Big Adventure]]}}
** '''Player:''' I'll get started right away then! What made you come here to run a cooking competition?
** '''My Arm:''' My Arm is a good farmer now, so want to see what can be made with stuff from farms.
** '''My Arm:''' Humans make lots of different foods, so My Arm can learn about them all here, even though human food is bad.
** '''My Arm:''' Then I can make Snowflake nice food when I go home.
** '''Player:''' I'm sure she would like that! And human food isn't all bad!
** '''Player:''' So, how does the competition work?
* '''My Arm:''' You must cook me best dish from things in cupboard. Best dish wins.
* '''Player:''' What sort of thing should I be making?
* '''My Arm:''' Dat is not for me to tell human, you must get it right yourself.
* '''My Arm:''' Make sure it exciting, and exotic. Humans are bad cooks, so make sure it not boring like most human stuffs.
* '''My Arm:''' You get one try, so make sure you do good try.
* '''My Arm:''' Good luck. My Arm need judge other contestants now.
* {{tact|My Arm wanders off to check some of the other contestants entries.}}
* '''Player:''' I only get one try, so I need to make sure I do a good job. I should talk to the other contestants first and see what they did before I start cooking.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Cook===
* '''Player:''' Hi cook!
* '''Cook:''' Hello, [player name]. Are you taking part in the cookout?
* '''Player:''' I am! Do you have any advice for me? I'm not sure what to cook.
* '''Cook:''' Normally I wouldn't share my secrets, but since this is all for fun, I'll make an exception.
* '''Cook:''' I made one of my finest pizzas. Lovely base, juiciest tomatoes, the cheesiest of cheeses.
* '''Player:''' Did My Arm like it? It sounds really good!
* '''Cook:''' That's the thing, he didn't like it! He said it was exciting, but wasn't exotic enough.
* '''Player:''' That is interesting. Thanks for the information.
* '''Cook:''' Good luck!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hans===
* '''Player:''' Hi, Hans!
* '''Hans:''' Hello.
* '''Player:''' I'm a bit stuck on what to make, do you have any ideas for me?
* '''Hans:''' No, I'm working on my own thing. I think I might be on to something, and I want to win!
* '''Player:''' Fair enough. Good luck.
* '''Hans:''' You too.
* {{tact|end}}

====When using the right-click Age option====
* '''Hans:''' You've spent...
* '''Hans:''' ...I have no idea. I'm too busy to figure this out right now. Ask me again later.

===Talking to the Wise Old Man===
* '''Player:''' Hello sir!
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Hi, [player name]. I see you've joined the cookout!
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Any idea what you're going to make?
* '''Player:''' None at all. I was actually hoping you might have an idea for me.
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Well, it is a competition, but I'd like to see someone win, and that isn't going to be me.
* '''Player:''' Why wouldn't it be you?
* '''Wise Old Man:''' I've already submitted my entry, and it didn't win! I submitted a banana.
* '''Player:''' Just a... banana? Nothing else?
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Yes! I thought that, since My Arm is a troll, they may not have seen a banana before, so might think it's a very clever dish.
* '''Wise Old Man:''' He actually said it was rather boring. Nice and exotic, but boring.
* '''Player:''' It was a clever idea. So I need to do something more exciting than a banana.
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Yes. I don't know what that is though, you'll have to figure that out.
* '''Player:''' Thanks for the help.
* {{tact|end}}

===After talking to all three contestants===
* '''Player:''' So, I need to make something exciting and exotic.
* '''Player:''' Hmm... and a pizza isn't exotic enough, and a banana isn't exciting enough.
* '''Player:''' I wonder if I could... somehow get something both exciting and exotic out of that information.
* '''Player:''' Time to look and see what ingredients I can find in the cupboard.
* {{tact|end}}

===Cooking pizza===
* {{tcond|Cooking plain pizza:}}
** '''Player:''' The cook said that My Arm thought his plain pizza wasn't exotic enough. Maybe I can do something to make it more exotic?
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|Adding banana to pizza:}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I don't know who would ever eat this, but it's certainly exciting and exotic!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|Burning banana pizza:}}
